reviews.text: Very easy to use and there is always someone at the ticket office
Best station I’ve visited for many years. I chose the carpaccio to begin which was delicious, followed by the sea bream. Service brilliant and the wine list also worthy of note. Thank you Buckshaw.
You can't give Northern staff grief because trains are running late or are cancelled, especially if its a technical issue which is Network Rails responsibility...
Well functioning plenty of parking that's free. Too busy at peak times not much seating. Would be nice to have a place to get a brew but no complaints

Terrible station. Why have a lift that’s often not working. If you’re unlucky enough to arrive on the last train (usually because earlier train was cancelled) the staff are very impatient for you to exit so they can go home, but with the lift not working be careful they don’t lock you in. This nearly happened to us, disgusted they don’t check everyone has left.  Boasts a “big” car park but is always overflowing on week days with cars parked all down nearby roads causing a hazard.
